    <subsection>
        <title>2.1 - Separable Equations</title>
        <p> In this section, students will learn to classify and solve separable equations. This satisfies module objectives 1 and 2.
            <ol>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/8YZxHOLRtlw">🎥Video 2.1.1</url> (2:15). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/346938">✅Checkpoint 2.1.1</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/SCw2e0B6g8w">🎥Video 2.1.2</url> (3:54). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/346944">✅Checkpoint 2.1.2</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> 🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Problems 2-22 (alternating evens) in Exercises 2.2 (pg. 50). </p></li> 
            </ol>
        </p>
    </subsection>

    <subsection>
        <title>2.2 - Linear Equations</title>
        <p> In this section, students will learn to write linear equations and standard form and find their general solutions by using integrating factors. This satisfies module objectives 1 and 4.
            <ol>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/JanbO63I3qA">🎥Video 2.2.1</url> (3:09). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/348024">✅Checkpoint 2.2.1</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/zs-1vviWWJY">🎥Video 2.2.2</url> (10:05). </p></li>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/I_1gtyGqMKk">🎥Video 2.2.3</url> (6:19). </p></li>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/H5UsKOkCO9c">🎥Video 2.2.4</url> (6:29). </p></li>
                <li><p> 🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Problems 2-24 (alternating evens) in Exercises 2.2 (pg. 60-61). </p></li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </subsection>

    <subsection>
        <title>2.3 - Exact Equations</title>
        <p> In this section, students will learn to classify and solve exact equations. This satisfies module objectives 1 and 3.
            <ol>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/2clAykwSJQY">🎥Video 2.3.1</url> (6:37). </p></li>
                <li><p> Complete the <url href="https://canvas.svsu.edu/courses/93320/quizzes/348022">✅Checkpoint 2.3.1</url>. </p></li> 
                <li><p> 🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Problems 2-26 (alternating evens) in Exercises 2.3 (pg. 68-69). </p></li> 
            </ol>
        </p>
    </subsection>
    

    <subsection>
        <title>2.4 - Substitution</title>
        <p>
            In this section, students will learn how to simplify first-order differential equations using substitution. This satisfies module objective 5.
            <ol>
                <li><p> Watch <url href="https://youtu.be/C_2T2ubZ6tQ">🎥Video 2.4.1</url> (4:46). </p></li>
                <li><p>🎯 <alert> Practice: </alert> Problems 2-10 (evens) in Exercises 2.5 (pg. 74).</p></li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </subsection>
</section>
